NAME
    App::cryp::exchange - Interact with cryptoexchanges

VERSION
    This document describes version 0.004 of App::cryp::exchange (from Perl
    distribution App-cryp-exchange), released on 2018-06-06.

SYNOPSIS
    Please see included script cryp-exchange.

FUNCTIONS
  get_order_book
    Usage:

     get_order_book(%args) -> [status, msg, result, meta]

    Get order book on an exchange.

    This function is not exported.

    Arguments ('*' denotes required arguments):

    *   exchange* => *str*

    *   pair* => *str*

    *   type => *str*

    Returns an enveloped result (an array).

    First element (status) is an integer containing HTTP status code (200
    means OK, 4xx caller error, 5xx function error). Second element (msg) is
    a string containing error message, or 'OK' if status is 200. Third
    element (result) is optional, the actual result. Fourth element (meta)
    is called result metadata and is optional, a hash that contains extra
    information.

    Return value: (any)

  list_accounts
    Usage:

     list_accounts(%args) -> [status, msg, result, meta]

    List exchange accounts.

    This function is not exported.

    Arguments ('*' denotes required arguments):

    *   detail => *bool*

    Returns an enveloped result (an array).

    First element (status) is an integer containing HTTP status code (200
    means OK, 4xx caller error, 5xx function error). Second element (msg) is
    a string containing error message, or 'OK' if status is 200. Third
    element (result) is optional, the actual result. Fourth element (meta)
    is called result metadata and is optional, a hash that contains extra
    information.

    Return value: (any)

